				<p>Massillon Council 554 meets on the second and fourth Tuesday, at 7:00 PM at the Knights of Columbus hall. In lieu of the fourth Tuesday meeting, there will be a social gathering. The Officers and Trustees of the council meet on the fourth Tuesday of every month at 6:30 PM. 
				<br><br>
				Council 554 is also a member of the Stark County Chapter Knights of Columbus and attend their meetings on the second Thursday of every month, except December. 
				<br><br>
				Council 554 also publishes a bi-monthly newsletter, which is mailed to every member. 
				<br><br>
				The following activities and programs are conducted annually by Council 554 and held at our Knights of Columbus hall:
					<li>Hot Lunch Program for the needy every Wednesday from 10:45AM to 12:00PM</li>
					<li>First and Second Degrees held frequently, conducted by the councils own degree teams</li>
					<li>Family Picnic on the first Sunday in August</li>
					<li>Children's Halloween Party in October</li>
					<li>Memorial Mass on the fourth Tuesday in November</li>
					<li>Children's Christmas Party in December</li>
					<li>New Year's Eve Party on December 31</li>
					<li>Basketball Free-Throw Contest in January (for boys and girls age 9 to 14)</li>
					<li>Anniversary Dinner in January</li>
					<li>Past Grand Knights Recognition Dinner in spring</li>
					<li>Children's Easter Egg Hunt</li>
					<li>"Excellence in Religion" Awards, for area youths presently in April</li>
					<li>Sponsor's numerous Bloodmobile Drives throughout the year</li>
					<li>Fraternal Night Party for members and wives, on fourth Tuesday in June</li>
					<li>Various service projects for local parishes (Round Table Program)</li>
				<br>
				Massillon Council 554 takes an active part in the Ohio State Council Knights of Columbus Service Program contest. In addition, the members of Council 554 take an active part in Supreme Council's "Surge with Service" program. Both promote and encourage service activities for Council, Church, Community, Family and Youth. 
